Police officers from Thika West subcounty should stop encroaching into Juja and harassing residents of Witeithie estate, Juja subcounty deputy commissioner Muthama Wambua (pictured) has said. All police issues in this estate should be handled by police from Juja, he said yesterday at a baraza. If Thika police are tracking criminals from their area into Juja, they should liaise with Juja officers, he added.Thika police boss Erastus Muthama said Witeithie is no longer in his jurisdiction. He said he would deal with officers encroaching into Witeithie.